I know the owl is a symbol used by Drake but theres deep spiritual significance as well. The Hebrew word for owl is Lillith, who is a demonic spirit associated with sexual lust. Which is related to Aphroditie from Greece and Ashteroth from Cannanite witchcraft. Also, the statue at Bohemian Grove is an owl but named Moloch who was originally called Molech a god worshipped by the Ammonites and was depicted at a bull. They would make the statue out of iron and a fire would be built in the bottom and they would throw their children alive in the fire because that's what Molech demanded. The combination of Moloch with the symbol of an owl at Bohemian grove is very telling because sexual immorality leads to unwanted children which would be more willingly offered as sacrifice to molech.
